    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This investment-grade FD3S Mazda RX-7 is a masterclass in 90s engineering, featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine in its original, unmodified configuration. The powertrain delivers seamless boost across the rev range, paired with a short-throw five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains incredibly rigid, preserving the celebrated 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry. Every vacuum line, apex seal, and cooling component has been maintained to exacting standards. Finished in its original high-luster paint with a cockpit-focused interior that shows zero UV degradation or bolster wear, this specimen offers a visceral, analog driving experience that is increasingly impossible to find in this state of preservation.",
